First Read: 19-Mar-26
SB374 Enrolled
1 Enrolled, An Act,
2
3 To propose an amendment to the Constitution of Alabama
4 of 2022, relating to Henry County, to levy an ad valorem tax
5 of three mills south of Sandy Creek for public school purposes
6 in Headland.
7 BE IT ENACTED BY THE LEGISLATURE OF ALABAMA:
8 Section 1. The following amendment to the Constitution
9 of Alabama of 2022, is proposed:
10 PROPOSED AMENDMENT
11 (a) In addition to all other ad valorem taxes,
12 beginning with the tax year for which taxes become due and
13 payable on October 1, 2027, and continuing through September
14 30, 2034, there is levied an ad valorem tax on all taxable
15 property located in Henry County and south of Sandy Creek at a
16 rate of three mills per dollar of assessed value.
17 (b) The proceeds of the tax shall be used exclusively
18 for public school purposes for projects in Headland.
19 Upon ratification of this constitutional amendment, the
20 Code Commissioner shall number and place this amendment as
21 appropriate in the constitution omitting this instructional
22 paragraph and may make the following nonsubstantive revisions:
23 change capitalization, hierarchy, spelling, and punctuation
24 for purposes of style and uniformity; correct manifest
25 grammatical, clerical, and typographical errors; revise
26 internal or external citations and cross-references; harmonize
27 language; and translate effective dates.
28 END PROPOSED AMENDMENT
Page 1

END PROPOSED AMENDMENT
SB374 Enrolled
29 Section 2. An election upon the proposed amendment
30 shall be held in accordance with Sections 284, 284.01, and 285
31 of the Constitution of Alabama of 2022, and the election laws
32 of this state. The appropriate election official shall assign
33 a ballot number for the proposed constitutional amendment on
34 the election ballot and shall set forth the following
35 description of the substance or subject matter of the proposed
36 constitutional amendment:
37 "Relating to Henry County, proposing an amendment to
38 the Constitution of Alabama of 2022, to levy a temporary ad
39 valorem tax of three mills on taxable property located south
40 of Sandy Creek to support public school projects in Headland.
41 Proposed by Act ____."
42 This description shall be followed by the following
43 language:
44 "Yes( ) No( )."
45 Section 3. The proposed amendment shall become valid as
46 part of the Constitution of Alabama of 2022, when approved by
47 a majority of the qualified electors voting thereon.
